Add LdapSsl optional User Mapping parameters.

Add destinationport for use with trap type alerts. Remove range from ilomCtrlEventLogRecordID.

ILOMCtrlSessionsConnectionType.name: ILOMCtrlSessionsConnectionType
ILOMCtrlSessionsConnectionType.description: An enumerated value which describes possible connection types by which a user can be log in.

ILOMCtrlLocalUserUsername.name: ILOMCtrlLocalUserUsername
ILOMCtrlLocalUserUsername.description: A local user username. This must start with an alphabetical letter and may contain alphabetical letters, digits, hyphens and underscores. This can not be 'password'. This can not contain spaces.

ILOMCtrlUserRole.name: ILOMCtrlUserRole
ILOMCtrlUserRole.description: An enumerated value which describes possible privilege levels (also known as roles) a user can have. ***NOTE: this textual-convention is deprecated and replaced by ILOMCtrlUserRoles.

ILOMCtrlResetAction.name: ILOMCtrlResetAction

ILOMCtrlNetworkIpDiscovery.name: ILOMCtrlNetworkIpDiscovery

ILOMCtrlEventLogType.name: ILOMCtrlEventLogType

ilomCtrlRemoteSyslogDest1.name: ilomCtrlRemoteSyslogDest1

ilomCtrlSshDsaKeyLength.name: ilomCtrlSshDsaKeyLength

ilomCtrlSshEnabled.name: ilomCtrlSshEnabled

ilomCtrlSingleSignonEnabled.name: ilomCtrlSingleSignonEnabled
ilomCtrlSingleSignonEnabled.description: Specified whether single sign-on authentication should be enabled on the device. Single sign-on allows tokens to be passed around so that it is not necessary to re-enter passwords between different applications. This would allow single sign-on between the SC web interface and the SP web interface, between the SC command-line interface and the SP command-line interface, and between the SC and SP interfaces and the Java Remote Console application.

ilomCtrlNetworkTable.name: ilomCtrlNetworkTable
ilomCtrlNetworkTable.description: A table listing all targets whose networks can be controlled.

ilomCtrlNetworkEntry.name: ilomCtrlNetworkEntry
ilomCtrlNetworkEntry.description: An entry for a target which can be reset.

ilomCtrlNetworkTarget.name: ilomCtrlNetworkTarget
ilomCtrlNetworkTarget.description: This is the nomenclature name for a target which has a configurable network. On some systems, there are multiple targets which have networks. On a traditional, non-blade system, this table will contain only one row for the network configuration of the service processor, which has a nomenclature name of '/SP'. On blade systems, this table will contain multiple rows. There will be a row for '/SC' which allows for configuration of the system controller's network settings. In addition, there will be rows for each blade's service processor. For example, a blade's service processor nomenclature takes the form of '/CH/BL0/SP', '/CH/BL1/SP' and so on. This will allow for the configuration of the service processors from the system controller. In the case of redundant system controllers, the floating master IP addressed can be configured using a name of /MASTERSC.

ilomCtrlNetworkMacAddress.name: ilomCtrlNetworkMacAddress
ilomCtrlNetworkMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of the service processor or system controller.

ilomCtrlNetworkIpDiscovery.name: ilomCtrlNetworkIpDiscovery
ilomCtrlNetworkIpDiscovery.description: Specifies whether the current target is configured to have static IP settings or whether these settings are retrieved dynamically from DHCP.

ilomCtrlNetworkIpAddress.name: ilomCtrlNetworkIpAddress
ilomCtrlNetworkIpAddress.description: Indicates the current IP address for the given target.

ilomCtrlNetworkIpGateway.name: ilomCtrlNetworkIpGateway
ilomCtrlNetworkIpGateway.description: Indicates the current IP gateway for the given target.

ilomCtrlNetworkIpNetmask.name: ilomCtrlNetworkIpNetmask
ilomCtrlNetworkIpNetmask.description: Indicates the current IP netmask for the given target.

ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpDiscovery.name: ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpDiscovery
ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpDiscovery.description: This property is used to set the pending value for the mode of IP discovery for the given target. The possible values are static(1) or dynamic(2). Static values can be specified by setting the other pending properties in this table: ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpAddress, ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpGateway, and ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpNetmask. If dynamic is specified, the other pending properties should not be set. This property does not take effect until the ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending property is set to true for the given row.

ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpAddress.name: ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpAddress
ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpAddress.description: This property is used to set the pending IP address for the given target. This property does not take effect until the ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending property is set to true for the given row.

ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpGateway.name: ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpGateway
ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpGateway.description: This property is used to set the pending IP gateway for the given target. This property does not take effect until the ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending property is set to true for the given row.

ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpNetmask.name: ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpNetmask
ilomCtrlNetworkPendingIpNetmask.description: This property is used to set the pending IP netmask for the given target. This property does not take effect until the ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending property is set to true for the given row.

ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending.name: ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending
ilomCtrlNetworkCommitPending.description: This property is used to commit pending properties for the given row. Settings this property to true(1) will cause the network to be reconfigured according to the values specified in the other pending properties.

ilomCtrlNetworkOutOfBandMacAddress.name: ilomCtrlNetworkOutOfBandMacAddress
ilomCtrlNetworkOutOfBandMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of the out of band management interface (where applicable)

ilomCtrlNetworkSidebandMacAddress.name: ilomCtrlNetworkSidebandMacAddress
ilomCtrlNetworkSidebandMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of the sideband management interface (where applicable)

ilomCtrlNetworkPendingManagementPort.name: ilomCtrlNetworkPendingManagementPort

ilomCtrlNetworkManagementPort.name: ilomCtrlNetworkManagementPort
ilomCtrlNetworkManagementPort.description: Indicates the current managment port for the given target

ilomCtrlNetworkDHCPServerAddr.name: ilomCtrlNetworkDHCPServerAddr
ilomCtrlNetworkDHCPServerAddr.description: The address of the DHCP server for this row.

ilomCtrlNetworkState.name: ilomCtrlNetworkState
ilomCtrlNetworkState.description: Specifies whether or not the row is enabled.

ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthTable.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthTable

ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthUsername.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthUsername
ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthUsername.description: The username of a local user on the device. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with ilomCtrlLocalUserUsername.

ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthPassword.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthPassword
ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthPassword.description: The password of a local user on the device. This property is essentially write-only. The write-only access level is no longer supported as of SNMPv2. This property must return a null value when read. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with ilomCtrlLocalUserPassword.

ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthRole.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthRole
ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthRole.description: Specifies whether a user's password is assigned or unassigned. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with ilomCtrlLocalUserRoles.

ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthRowStatus.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthRowStatus
ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table. This property can be set to either createAndWait(5) or destroy(6), to create and remove a user respectively. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with ilomCtrlLocalUserRowStatus.

ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthCLIMode.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthCLIMode
ilomCtrlLocalUserAuthCLIMode.description: Allows the CLI mode to be configured on a per-user basis. The CLI mode determines which shell the user will interact with. If the 'default' mode is select, the user will see the DMTF CLP after logging in via ssh or the console. If the 'alom' mode is selected, the user will see the ALOM CMT shell after logging in via ssh or the console. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with ilomCtrlLocalUserCLIMode.

ilomCtrlLocalUserTable.description: This table provides a listing of the current local users on a system along with their password state.

ilomCtrlLocalUserEntry.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserEntry
ilomCtrlLocalUserEntry.description: An entry containing objects for a local user in the database.

ilomCtrlLocalUserUsername.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserUsername
ilomCtrlLocalUserUsername.description: The username of a local user on the device.

ilomCtrlLocalUserPassword.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserPassword
ilomCtrlLocalUserPassword.description: The password of a local user on the device. This property is essentially write-only. The write-only access level is no longer supported as of SNMPv2. This property must return a null value when read.

ilomCtrlLocalUserRoles.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserRoles
ilomCtrlLocalUserRoles.description: Specifies the role that is associated with a user. ilomCtrlLocalUserCLIMode.name: ilomCtrlLocalUserCLIMode
ilomCtrlLocalUserCLIMode.description: Allows the CLI mode to be configured on a per-user basis. The CLI mode determines which shell the user will interact with. If the 'default' mode is select, the user will see the DMTF CLP after logging in via ssh or the console. If the 'alom' mode is selected, the user will see the ALOM CMT shell after logging in via ssh or the console.

ilomCtrlSessionsTable.name: ilomCtrlSessionsTable

ilomCtrlSessionsUsername.name: ilomCtrlSessionsUsername

ilomCtrlSessionsConnectionType.name: ilomCtrlSessionsConnectionType

ilomCtrlSessionsLoginTime.name: ilomCtrlSessionsLoginTime

ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtVersion.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtVersion
ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtVersion.description: The version of the current firmware image.

ilomCtrlFirmwareBuildNumber.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareBuildNumber
ilomCtrlFirmwareBuildNumber.description: The build number of the current firmware image.

ilomCtrlFirmwareBuildDate.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareBuildDate
ilomCtrlFirmwareBuildDate.description: The build date and time of the current firmware image.

ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPServerIP.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPServerIP
ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPServerIP.description: The IP address of the TFTP server which will be used to download the the firmware image.

ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPFileName.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPFileName
ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPFileName.description: The relative path of the new firmware image file on the TFTP server.

ilomCtrlFirmwarePreserveConfig.name: ilomCtrlFirmwarePreserveConfig
ilomCtrlFirmwarePreserveConfig.description: This property determines whether the previous configuration of the device should be preserved after a firmware update. The configuration data includes all users information, configuration of clients and services, and any logs. The default value of this property is true.

ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtStatus.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtStatus
ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtStatus.description: This property indicates the status of a firmware update. If a TFTP error occurred while attempting to upload a new firmware image, the value of this property will be tftpError(1). If the image was uploaded correctly but it did not pass verification, the value of this property will be imageVerificationFailed(2). Otherwise, the status will indicate that the update is inProgress(3) or is a success(4). A firmware update could take as long as 20 minutes. During this time, no other operations should be performed on the device. Upon success, the device will be reset.

ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtAction.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtAction
ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtAction.description: This property is used to initiate a firmware update using the values of the other firmware management properties as parameters. It can also clear the values of those parameters. To initiate a firmware update, set the value of this property to initate(2). To clear the values of the writeable firmware management properties, set this propery to clearProperties(1). Before initiating a firmware update, the ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPServerIP, ilomCtrlFirmwareTFTPFileName, and ilomCtrlFirmwarePreserveConfig properties must be set. After intiating a firmware update, the ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtStatus property can be used to determine if the operation was successful. This is effectively a write-only property.

ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtFilesystemVersion.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtFilesystemVersion
ilomCtrlFirmwareMgmtFilesystemVersion.description: The version of the current file system.

ilomCtrlFirmwareDelayBIOS.name: ilomCtrlFirmwareDelayBIOS
ilomCtrlFirmwareDelayBIOS.description: On servers that support a BIOS, this property is used to postpone the BIOS upgrade until the next server poweroff. Setting this property to 'false' will cause the server to be forced off if a BIOS upgrade is necessary. The default value of this property is false.

ilomCtrlEventLogRecordID.name: ilomCtrlEventLogRecordID

ilomCtrlEventLogType.name: ilomCtrlEventLogType

ilomCtrlEventLogTimestamp.name: ilomCtrlEventLogTimestamp
ilomCtrlEventLogTimestamp.description: The date and time that the event log entry was recorded.

ilomCtrlEventLogClass.name: ilomCtrlEventLogClass
ilomCtrlEventLogClass.description: An integer representing the class of event.

ilomCtrlEventLogSeverity.name: ilomCtrlEventLogSeverity
ilomCtrlEventLogSeverity.description: The event severity corresponding to the given log entry.

ilomCtrlEventLogDescription.name: ilomCtrlEventLogDescription
ilomCtrlEventLogDescription.description: A textual description of the event.

ilomCtrlEventLogClear.name: ilomCtrlEventLogClear
ilomCtrlEventLogClear.description: When set to 'true' clears the event log.

ilomCtrlAlertsTable.name: ilomCtrlAlertsTable
ilomCtrlAlertsTable.description: This table is used to view and add alert rules.

ilomCtrlAlertsEntry.name: ilomCtrlAlertsEntry
ilomCtrlAlertsEntry.description: An entry containing objects for an alert rule.

ilomCtrlAlertID.name: ilomCtrlAlertID
ilomCtrlAlertID.description: An integer ID associated with a given alert rule.

ilomCtrlAlertSeverity.name: ilomCtrlAlertSeverity
ilomCtrlAlertSeverity.description: This property specifies the mininum event severity which should trigger an alert, for a given class.

ilomCtrlAlertType.name: ilomCtrlAlertType
ilomCtrlAlertType.description: This property specifies the type of notification for a given alert. If the type is snmptrap(2) or ipmipet(3), the ilomCtrlAlertDestinationIP must be specified. If the type is email(1), the ilomCtrlAlertDestinationEmail must be specified.

ilomCtrlAlertDestinationIP.name: ilomCtrlAlertDestinationIP
ilomCtrlAlertDestinationIP.description: This property species the IP address to send alert notifications when the alert type is snmptrap(2), ipmipet(3), or remotesyslog(4).

ilomCtrlAlertDestinationEmail.name: ilomCtrlAlertDestinationEmail
ilomCtrlAlertDestinationEmail.description: This property species the email address to send alert notifications when the alert type is email(1).

ilomCtrlAlertSNMPVersion.name: ilomCtrlAlertSNMPVersion
ilomCtrlAlertSNMPVersion.description: The version of SNMP trap that should be used for the given alert rule.

ilomCtrlAlertSNMPCommunityOrUsername.name: ilomCtrlAlertSNMPCommunityOrUsername
ilomCtrlAlertSNMPCommunityOrUsername.description: This string specifies the community string to be used when the ilomCtrlAlertSNMPVersion property is set to 'v1' or 'v2c'. Alternatively, this string specifies the SNMP username to use when the ilomCtrlAlertSNMPVersion is set to 'v3'.

ilomCtrlAlertDestinationPort.name: ilomCtrlAlertDestinationPort
ilomCtrlAlertDestinationPort.description: Destination port for SNMP traps, 0 maps to the default

ilomCtrlAlertEmailEventClassFilter.name: ilomCtrlAlertEmailEventClassFilter
ilomCtrlAlertEmailEventClassFilter.description: A class name or 'all' to filter emailed alerts on.

ilomCtrlAlertEmailEventTypeFilter.name: ilomCtrlAlertEmailEventTypeFilter
ilomCtrlAlertEmailEventTypeFilter.description: A type name or 'all' to filter emailed alerts on.

ilomCtrlAlertEmailCustomSender.name: ilomCtrlAlertEmailCustomSender
ilomCtrlAlertEmailCustomSender.description: An optional format to identify the sender or the 'from' address. Customizing this string allows the user to specify the exact contents (up to 80 chars) of the 'from' field in the email message. Either one of the substitution strings '<IPADDRESS>' or '<HOSTNAME>' can be used as needed. By default, this parameter is an empty string, which results in the standard ILOM formatted originator for the alerts. e.g., ilom-sp@sp1302.dev.sun.com, sun-ilom@[<IPADDRESS>], or ilom-alert@<HOSTNAME>.abc.com

ilomCtrlAlertEmailMessagePrefix.name: ilomCtrlAlertEmailMessagePrefix
ilomCtrlAlertEmailMessagePrefix.description: An optional string that can be added to the beginning of the message body. The prefix size can be up to 80 characters.

ilomCtrlDateAndTime.name: ilomCtrlDateAndTime
ilomCtrlDateAndTime.description: The date and time of the device.

ilomCtrlNTPEnabled.name: ilomCtrlNTPEnabled
ilomCtrlNTPEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not Network Time Protocol is enabled.

ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortPresent.name: ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortPresent
ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortPresent.description: Indicates whether the given device has an internal serial port that is configurable. The internal serial port is the connection between the host server and the service processor that allows the SP to access the host serial console.

ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortBaudRate.name: ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortBaudRate
ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortBaudRate.description: Specifies the current baud rate setting for the internal serial port. This is only readable/settable if ilomCtrlSerialInternalPortPresent is true.

ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortPresent.name: ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortPresent
ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortPresent.description: Indicates whether the given device has an external serial port that is configurable.

ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortBaudRate.name: ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortBaudRate
ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortBaudRate.description: Specifies the current baud rate setting for the external serial port. This is only readable/settable if ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortPresent is true.

ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortFlowControl.name: ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortFlowControl
ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortFlowControl.description: Specifies the current flowcontrol setting for the external serial port. This is only readable/settable if ilomCtrlSerialExternalPortPresent is true.

ilomCtrlPowerTable.name: ilomCtrlPowerTable
ilomCtrlPowerTable.description: A table listing all targets whose power can be controlled.

ilomCtrlPowerEntry.name: ilomCtrlPowerEntry
ilomCtrlPowerEntry.description: An entry for a power-controllable target.

ilomCtrlPowerTarget.name: ilomCtrlPowerTarget
ilomCtrlPowerTarget.description: This is the nomenclature name for a target which supports power control. On some systems, there are multiple targets which support power control. On a traditional, non-blade system, this table will contain only one row. The nomenclature name for a traditional server is '/SYS'. On blade systems, this table will contain multiple rows. There will be a row for '/CH' which allows for power control of the entire chassis. In addition, there will be rows for each blade. Blade nomenclature takes the form of '/CH/BL0/SYS', '/CH/BL1/SYS', and so on.

ilomCtrlPowerAction.name: ilomCtrlPowerAction
ilomCtrlPowerAction.description: The action to apply to the given power control target. The possible actions are powerOn(1), powerOff(2), powerCycle(3), and powerSoft(4). When this value is read, it returns a null value.

ilomCtrlResetTable.name: ilomCtrlResetTable
ilomCtrlResetTable.description: A table listing all targets which can be reset.

ilomCtrlResetEntry.name: ilomCtrlResetEntry
ilomCtrlResetEntry.description: An entry for a target which can be reset.

ilomCtrlResetTarget.name: ilomCtrlResetTarget
ilomCtrlResetTarget.description: This is the nomenclature name for a target which supports reset capabilities. On some systems, there are multiple targets which support reset. On most systems, only system controllers and service processors support reset. On a traditional, non-blade system, this table will contain only one row, representing its service processor. The nomenclature name for a traditional server's service processor is '/SP'. On blade systems, this table will contain multiple rows. There will be a row for '/SC' which allows for reset of the system controller. In addition, there will be rows for each blade's service processor. For example, a blade's service processor nomenclature takes the form of '/CH/BL0/SP', '/CH/BL1/SP' and so on.

ilomCtrlResetAction.name: ilomCtrlResetAction
ilomCtrlResetAction.description: The action to apply to the given reset control target. The possible actions are reset(1), which is a normal reset, resetNonMaskableInterrupt(2) which is a forced reset, and force(3) which is a forced reset for platforms that do not support NMI. When this value is read, it returns a null value.

ilomCtrlRedundancyStatus.name: ilomCtrlRedundancyStatus
ilomCtrlRedundancyStatus.description: This property indicates the status of the device in a redundant configuration. It may be active(2) or standby(3) when configured as a redundant pair or standAlone(4) if it does not have a peer. In addition, it may be in a state called initializing(1) if it is in a transitional state.

ilomCtrlRedundancyAction.name: ilomCtrlRedundancyAction
ilomCtrlRedundancyAction.description: This action is used to promote or demote this device from active or standy status.

ilomCtrlRedundancyFRUName.name: ilomCtrlRedundancyFRUName
ilomCtrlRedundancyFRUName.description: FRU Name of the CMM on which this agent is running.

ilomCtrlPolicyTable.name: ilomCtrlPolicyTable
ilomCtrlPolicyTable.description: A table listing all policies that can be administered.

ilomCtrlPolicyEntry.name: ilomCtrlPolicyEntry
ilomCtrlPolicyEntry.description: An entry for a policy which can be enabled or disabled.

ilomCtrlPolicyId.name: ilomCtrlPolicyId
ilomCtrlPolicyId.description: An integer identifier of the policy.

ilomCtrlPolicyShortStr.name: ilomCtrlPolicyShortStr
ilomCtrlPolicyShortStr.description: A short description of the policy.

ilomCtrlPolicyLongStr.name: ilomCtrlPolicyLongStr
ilomCtrlPolicyLongStr.description: A verbose description of the policy.

ilomCtrlPolicyEnabled.name: ilomCtrlPolicyEnabled
ilomCtrlPolicyEnabled.description: Indicates the status of the policy.

ilomCtrlResetToDefaultsAction.name: ilomCtrlResetToDefaultsAction
ilomCtrlResetToDefaultsAction.description: This property is used to initiate the action of restoring the configuration on the SP to the original factory default state.

ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreTargetURI.name: ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreTargetURI
ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreTargetURI.description: This property is used to set target destination of configuration xml file during backup and restore. The syntax is {protocol}://[user:passwword]@]host[/][path/][file] for example tftp://10.8.136.154/remotedir/config_backup.xml currently, the supported protocols are: scp, tftp. for certain protocol which needs password field, please use ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreProtocolPassword to set password.

ilomCtrlBackupAndRestorePassphrase.name: ilomCtrlBackupAndRestorePassphrase
ilomCtrlBackupAndRestorePassphrase.description: This property is used to set passphrase for encrypt/decrypt sensitive data during backup and restore. For snmpget, it returns null as value.

ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreAction.name: ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreAction
ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreAction.description: This property is used to issue a action, either backup or restore.

ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreActionStatus.name: ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreActionStatus
ilomCtrlBackupAndRestoreActionStatus.description: This property is used to monitor the current status of backup/restore.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsLevel.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsLevel
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsLevel.description: Indicates the level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with these: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnLevel, ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetLevel, ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetLevel While deprecated, this object will display advsettings(3), unless: - all 3 of the above are currently set to init(1), in which case this object will display min(1) - all 3 of the above are currently set to maximum(3), in which case this object will display max(2).

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsTrigger.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsTrigger
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsTrigger.description: Indicates the triggers of embedded diagnostics for the host.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsVerbosity.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsVerbosity
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsVerbosity.description: Indicates the verbosity level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with these: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnVerbosity, ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetVerbosity, ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetVerbosity. While deprecated, this object will display advsettings(3), unless: - all 3 of the above are currently set to minimum(1), in which case this object will display min(1) - all 3 of the above are currently set to maximum(3), in which case this object will display max(2).

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsMode.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsMode
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsMode.description: Indicates the modes for POST. POST will stop at the mode specified by this property.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnLevel.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnLevel
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnLevel.description: Indicates the level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for the power-on-reset trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetLevel.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetLevel
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetLevel.description: Indicates the level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for the user-reset trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetLevel.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetLevel
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetLevel.description: Indicates the level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for the error-reset trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnVerbosity.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnVerbosity
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsPowerOnVerbosity.description: Indicates the verbosity level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for power-on-reset trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetVerbosity.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetVerbosity
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsUserResetVerbosity.description: Indicates the verbosity level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for user-reset trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetVerbosity.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetVerbosity
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsErrorResetVerbosity.description: Indicates the verbosity level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for error-reset trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsStatus.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsStatus
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsStatus.description: Indicates the progress of POST diagnostics on the host, expressed as a percentage.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsAction.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsAction
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsAction.description: An action to take to control POST running on the host.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsHwChangeLevel.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsHwChangeLevel
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsHwChangeLevel.description: Indicates the level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for the hw-change trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsHwChangeVerbosity.name: ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsHwChangeVerbosity
ilomCtrlSPARCDiagsHwChangeVerbosity.description: Indicates the verbosity level of embedded diagnostics that should be run on the host during a boot for hw-change trigger.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostMACAddress.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostMACAddress
ilomCtrlSPARCHostMACAddress.description: Displays the starting MAC address for the host.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostOBPVersion.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostOBPVersion
ilomCtrlSPARCHostOBPVersion.description: Displays the version string for OBP.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostPOSTVersion.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostPOSTVersion
ilomCtrlSPARCHostPOSTVersion.description: Displays the version string for POST.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostAutoRunOnError.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostAutoRunOnError
ilomCtrlSPARCHostAutoRunOnError.description: This option determines whether the host should continue to boot in the event of a non-fatal POST error.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostPOSTStatus.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostPOSTStatus
ilomCtrlSPARCHostPOSTStatus.description: A string that describes the status of POST. ***NOTE: OS Boot status is ilomCtrlSPARCHostOSBootStatus.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostAutoRestartPolicy.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostAutoRestartPolicy
ilomCtrlSPARCHostAutoRestartPolicy.description: This determines what action the SP should take when it discovers that the host is hung.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostOSBootStatus.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostOSBootStatus
ilomCtrlSPARCHostOSBootStatus.description: A string that describes the boot status of host OS.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootTimeout.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootTimeout
ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootTimeout.description: This is the boot timer time out value.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootRestart.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootRestart
ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootRestart.description: This determines what action the SP should take when the boot timer expires.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostMaxBootFail.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostMaxBootFail
ilomCtrlSPARCHostMaxBootFail.description: This is the number of max boot failures allowed.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootFailRecovery.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootFailRecovery
ilomCtrlSPARCHostBootFailRecovery.description: This determines what action the SP should take when the max boot failures are reached.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostHypervisorVersion.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostHypervisorVersion
ilomCtrlSPARCHostHypervisorVersion.description: Displays the version string for Hypervisor.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostSysFwVersion.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostSysFwVersion
ilomCtrlSPARCHostSysFwVersion.description: Displays the version string for SysFw.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostIoReconfigurePolicy.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostIoReconfigurePolicy
ilomCtrlSPARCHostIoReconfigurePolicy.description: This determines the host IO reconfiguration policy to apply on next host power-on.

ilomCtrlSPARCHostGMVersion.name: ilomCtrlSPARCHostGMVersion
ilomCtrlSPARCHostGMVersion.description: Displays the version string for Guest Manager.

ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeState.name: ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeState
ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeState.description: Configures the boot mode state for the host. Specifying 'normal' means that the host retains current NVRAM variable settings. Specifying 'resetNvram' means that all NVRAM settings will be reset to their default values.

ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeScript.name: ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeScript
ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeScript.description: Specifies the script to run when host boots.

ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeExpires.name: ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeExpires
ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeExpires.description: Displays the date and time for when the boot mode configuration should expire.

ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeLDOMConfig.name: ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeLDOMConfig
ilomCtrlSPARCBootModeLDOMConfig.description: This string refers to the config name value that must either be 'default' or match a named LDOM configuration downloaded to the service processor using the LDOM Manager.

ilomCtrlSPARCKeySwitchState.name: ilomCtrlSPARCKeySwitchState
ilomCtrlSPARCKeySwitchState.description: Specifies the current state of the virtual key switch.

ilomCtrlSystemIdentifier.name: ilomCtrlSystemIdentifier
ilomCtrlSystemIdentifier.description: This string, which is often the host name of the server associated with ILOM, will be sent out in the varbind for all traps that ILOM generates.

ilomCtrlHostName.name: ilomCtrlHostName
ilomCtrlHostName.description: This string is the hostname for ILOM.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryEnabled.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryEnabled
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the Active Directory client is enabled.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryIP.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryIP
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryIP.description: The IP address of the Active Directory server used as a name service for user accounts.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryPortNumber.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryPortNumber
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryPortNumber.description: Specifies the port number for the Active Directory client. Specifying 0 as the port means auto-select while specifying 1-65535 configures the actual port.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRole.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRole
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRole.description: Specifies the role that a user authenticated via Active Directory should have. Setting this property to 'Administrator' or 'Operator' will cause the Active Directory client to ignore the schema stored on the AD server. Setting this to 'none' clears the value and indicates that the native Active Directory schema should be used. ***NOTE: this object is deprecated and replaced with ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRoles.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertFileURI.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertFileURI
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertFileURI.description: This is the URI of a certificate file needed when Strict Cert Mode is enabled. Setting the URI causes the tranfer of the file, making the certificate available immediately for certificate authentication.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryTimeout.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryTimeout
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds to wait before timing out if the Active Directory Server is not responding.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryStrictCertEnabled.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryStrictCertEnabled
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryStrictCertEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the Strict Cert Mode is enabled for the Active Directory Client. If enabled, the Active Directory certificate must be uploaded to the SP so that certificate validation can be performed when communicating with the Active Directory server.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertFileStatus.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertFileStatus
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertFileStatus.description: A string indicating the status of the certificate file. This is useful in determining whether a certificate file is present or not.

ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainTable.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainTable
ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainTable.description: This table is used to configure domain information required for configuring the Active Directory client.

ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainEntry.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainEntry
ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainEntry.description: An entry for an Active Directory user domain.

ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainId.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainId
ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomainId.description: An integer identifier of the Active Directory domain.

ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomain.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomain
ilomCtrlActiveDirUserDomain.description: This string should match exactly with an authentication domain on the Active Directory server. This string should contain a substitution string '<USERNAME>' which will be replaced with the user's login name during authentication. Either the principle or distinguished name format is allowed.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupsTable.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupsTable
ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupsTable.description: This table is used to configure admin group information required for configuring the Active Directory client.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupsEntry.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupsEntry
ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupsEntry.description: An entry for an Active Directory admin group.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupId.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupId
ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupId.description: An integer identifier of the Active Directory admin group entry.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupName.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupName
ilomCtrlActiveDirAdminGroupName.description: This string should contain a distinguished name that exactly matches one of the group names on the ActiveDirectory server. Any user belonging to one of these groups in this table will be assigned the ILOM role of Administrator.

ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupsTable.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupsTable
ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupsTable.description: This table is used to configure operator group information required for configuring the Active Directory client.

ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupsEntry.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupsEntry
ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupsEntry.description: An entry for an Active Directory operator group.

ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupId.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupId
ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupId.description: An integer identifier of the Active Directory operator group entry.

ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupName.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupName
ilomCtrlActiveDirOperatorGroupName.description: This string should contain a distinguished name that exactly matches one of the group names on the ActiveDirectory server. Any user belonging to one of these groups in this table will be assigned the ILOM role of Operator.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerTable.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerTable
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerTable.description: This table is used to view and configure alternate server information for the Active Directory client.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerEntry.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerEntry
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerEntry.description: An entry for an Active Directory alternate server.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerId.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerId
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerId.description: An integer identifier of the Active Directory alternate server table.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerIp.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerIp
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerIp.description: The IP address of the Active Directory alternate server used as a name service for user accounts.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerPort.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerPort
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerPort.description: Specifies the port number for the Active Directory alternate server. Specifying 0 as the port indicates that auto-select will use the well known port number. Specifying 1-65535 is used to explicitly set the port number.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertStat.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertStatus
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertStat.description: A string indicating the status of the certificate file. This is useful in determining whether a certificate file is present or not.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertURI.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertURI
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertURI.description: This is the URI of a certificate file needed when Strict Cert Mode is enabled. Setting the URI causes the tranfer of the file, making the certificate available immediately for certificate authentication. Additionally, either 'remove' or 'restore' are supported for direct certificate manipulation.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertClea.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertClear
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertClea.description: A variable that will clear the certificate info associated with the server when it is set to true.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVers.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVersion
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVers.description: A string indicating the certificate version of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertSeri.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertSerialNo
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertSeri.description: A string showing the serial number of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertIssu.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertIssuer
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertIssu.description: A string showing the issuer of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertSubj.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertSubject
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertSubj.description: A string showing the subject of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVali.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertValidBegin
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVali.description: A string showing the valid start date of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVali.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertValidEnd
ilomCtrlActiveDirAlternateServerCertVali.description: A string showing the valid end date of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryLogDetail.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryLogDetail
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryLogDetail.description: Controls the amount of messages sent to the event log. The high priority has the least number of messages going to the log, while the lowest priority 'trace' has the most messages logged. When this object is set to 'none', no messages are logged.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRoles.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRoles
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryDefaultRoles.description: Specifies the role that a user authenticated via Active Directory should have. Setting this property to legacy roles of 'Administrator' or 'Operator', or any of the individual role IDs of 'a', 'u', 'c', 'r', 'o' and 's' will cause the Active Directory client to ignore the schema stored on the AD server. Setting this to 'none' clears the value and indicates that the native Active Directory schema should be used. The role IDs can be joined together 'aucros' where a-admin, u-user, c-console, r-reset, s-service and o-readOnly.

ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupsTable.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupsTable
ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupsTable.description: This table is used to configure custom group information required for configuring the Active Directory client.

ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupsEntry.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupsEntry
ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupsEntry.description: An entry for an Active Directory custom group.

ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupId.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupId
ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupId.description: An integer identifier of the Active Directory custom group entry.

ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupName.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupName
ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupName.description: This string should contain a distinguished name that exactly matches one of the group names on the ActiveDirectory server. Any user belonging to one of these groups in this table will be assigned the ILOM role based on the entry's configuration for roles.

ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupRoles.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupRoles
ilomCtrlActiveDirCustomGroupRoles.description: Specifies the role that a user authenticated via Active Directory should have. Setting this property to legacy roles of 'Administrator' or 'Operator', or any of the individual role IDs of 'a', 'u', 'c', 'r', 'o' and 's' will cause the Active Directory client to ignore the schema stored on the AD server. Setting this to 'none' clears the value and indicates that the native Active Directory schema should be used. The role IDs can be joined together 'aucros' where a-admin, u-user, c-console, r-reset, s-service and o-readOnly.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertClear.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertClear
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertClear.description: A variable that will clear the certificate info associated with the server when it is set to true.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertVersion.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertVersion
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertVersion.description: A string indicating the certificate version of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertSerialNo.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertSerialNo
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertSerialNo.description: A string showing the serial number of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertIssuer.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertIssuer
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertIssuer.description: A string showing the issuer of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertSubject.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertSubject
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertSubject.description: A string showing the subject of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertValidBegin.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertValidBegin
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertValidBegin.description: A string showing the valid start date of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertValidEnd.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertValidEnd
ilomCtrlActiveDirectoryCertValidEnd.description: A string showing the valid end date of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorEnabled.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorEnabled
ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the Active Directory DNS Locator functionality is enabled.

ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryTable.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryTable
ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryTable.description: This table is used to configure DNS Locator search queries used to locate the Active Directory server.

ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryEntry.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryEntry
ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryEntry.description: An entry for an Active Directory DNS Locator search query.

ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryId.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryId
ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryId.description: An integer identifier of the Active Directory DNS Locator Query entry.

ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryService.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryService
ilomCtrlActiveDirDnsLocatorQueryService.description: This string should contain the service name that will be used to perform the DNS query. The name may contain '<DOMAIN>' as a substitution marker, being replaced by the domain information associated for the user at the time of authentication. Also, the optional '<PORT: >' (ie <PORT:636> for standard LDAP/SSL port 636) can be used to override any learned port information if necessary.

ilomCtrlActiveDirExpSearchEnabled.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirExpSearchEnabled
ilomCtrlActiveDirExpSearchEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the Active Directory expanded search query functionality is enabled.

ilomCtrlActiveDirStrictCredentialErrorEn.name: ilomCtrlActiveDirStrictCredentialErrorEnabled
ilomCtrlActiveDirStrictCredentialErrorEn.description: Specifies whether or not user credential errors for Active Directory cause the user credentials to be completely errored out, or if the credential validation is attempted using any alternate server. When the parameter is true, the first user credential violation takes effect, but when the mode is false, the same user credentionals can be presented to other servers for authentication.

ilomCtrlSMTPEnabled.name: ilomCtrlSMTPEnabled
ilomCtrlSMTPEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the SMTP client is enabled.

ilomCtrlSMTPServerIP.name: ilomCtrlSMTPServerIP
ilomCtrlSMTPServerIP.description: The IP address of the SMTP server used as a name service for user accounts.

ilomCtrlSMTPPortNumber.name: ilomCtrlSMTPPortNumber
ilomCtrlSMTPPortNumber.description: Specifies the port number for the SMTP client.

ilomCtrlSMTPCustomSender.name: ilomCtrlSMTPCustomSender
ilomCtrlSMTPCustomSender.description: An optional format to identify the sender or the 'from' address. Customizing this string allows the user to specify the exact contents (up to 80 chars) of the 'from' field in the email message. Either one of the substitution strings '<IPADDRESS>' or '<HOSTNAME>' can be used as needed. e.g., ilom-sp@sp1302.dev.sun.com, sun-ilom@[<IPADDRESS>], or ilom-alert@<HOSTNAME>.abc.com. By default, this parameter is an empty string. The 'from' field is formatted by either: 1) alert-rule custom-sender, 2) smtp custom-sender, or 3) the standard ILOM originator.

ilomCtrlThdState.name: ilomCtrlThdState
ilomCtrlThdState.description: The state of the THD daemon.

ilomCtrlThdAction.name: ilomCtrlThdAction
ilomCtrlThdAction.description: Control action for THD daemon, either suspend or resume.

ilomCtrlThdModulesTable.name: ilomCtrlThdModulesTable
ilomCtrlThdModulesTable.description: A table listing the currently loaded THD modules.

ilomCtrlThdModulesEntry.name: ilomCtrlThdModulesEntry
ilomCtrlThdModulesEntry.description: An entry for a currently loaded THD module.

ilomCtrlThdModuleName.name: ilomCtrlThdModuleName
ilomCtrlThdModuleName.description: The name of the THD module.

ilomCtrlThdModuleDesc.name: ilomCtrlThdModuleDesc
ilomCtrlThdModuleDesc.description: The description of the THD module.

ilomCtrlThdModuleState.name: ilomCtrlThdModuleState
ilomCtrlThdModuleState.description: The state of the THD module.

ilomCtrlThdModuleAction.name: ilomCtrlThdModuleAction
ilomCtrlThdModuleAction.description: The control action for the THD module.

ilomCtrlThdInstanceTable.name: ilomCtrlThdInstanceTable
ilomCtrlThdInstanceTable.description: A table listing instances of currently loaded THD modules.

ilomCtrlThdInstanceEntry.name: ilomCtrlThdInstanceEntry
ilomCtrlThdInstanceEntry.description: An entry for a currently loaded THD module.

ilomCtrlThdModName.name: ilomCtrlThdModName
ilomCtrlThdModName.description: The name of the THD class of the instance.

ilomCtrlLdapSslEnabled.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslEnabled
ilomCtrlLdapSslEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the LDAP/SSL client is enabled.

ilomCtrlLdapSslIP.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslIP
ilomCtrlLdapSslIP.description: The IP address of the LDAP/SSL server used as a directory service for user accounts.

ilomCtrlLdapSslPortNumber.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslPortNumber
ilomCtrlLdapSslPortNumber.description: Specifies the port number for the LDAP/SSL client. Specifying 0 as the port means auto-select while specifying 1-65535 configures the actual port value.

ilomCtrlLdapSslDefaultRole.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslDefaultRole
ilomCtrlLdapSslDefaultRole.description: Specifies the role that a user authenticated via LDAP/SSL should have. Setting this property to 'Administrator' or 'Operator' will cause the LDAP/SSL client to ignore the schema stored on the server. The user will be granted the corresponding access level. Setting this to an empty string, or 'none' clears the value and indicates that the native LDAP/SSL schema should be used.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileURI.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileURI
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileURI.description: The tftp URI of the LDAP/SSL server's certificate file that should be uploaded in order to perform certificate validation. Setting the URI causes the tranfer of the specified file, making the certificate available immediately for certificate authentication. The server certificate file is needed when Strict Cert Mode is enabled. Additionally, either 'remove' or 'restore' are supported for direct certificate manipulation.

ilomCtrlLdapSslTimeout.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslTimeout
ilomCtrlLdapSslTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds to wait before timing out if the LDAP/SSL Server is not responding.

ilomCtrlLdapSslStrictCertEnabled.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslStrictCertEnabled
ilomCtrlLdapSslStrictCertEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the Strict Cert Mode is enabled for the LDAP/SSL Client. If enabled, the LDAP/SSL server's certificate must be uploaded to the SP so that certificate validation can be performed when communicating with the LDAP/SSL server.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileStatus.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileStatus
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileStatus.description: A string indicating the status of the certificate file. This is useful in determining whether a certificate file is present or not.

ilomCtrlLdapSslLogDetail.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslLogDetail
ilomCtrlLdapSslLogDetail.description: Controls the amount of messages sent to the event log. The high priority has the least number of messages going to the log, while the lowest priority 'trace' has the most messages logged. When this object is set to 'none', no messages are logged.

ilomCtrlLdapSslDefaultRoles.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslDefaultRoles
ilomCtrlLdapSslDefaultRoles.description: Specifies the role that a user authenticated via LDAP/SSL should have. Setting this property to legacy roles of 'Administrator' or 'Operator', or any of the individual role IDs of 'a', 'u', 'c', 'r', 'o' and 's' will cause the LDAP/SSL client to ignore the schema stored on the LDAP server. Setting this to 'none' clears the value and indicates that the native LDAP/SSL schema should be used. The role IDs can be joined together 'aucros' where a-admin, u-user, c-console, r-reset, s-service and o-readOnly.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileClear.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileClear
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileClear.description: A variable that will clear the certificate info associated with the server when it is set to true.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileVersion.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileVersion
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileVersion.description: A string indicating the certificate version of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileSerialNo.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileSerialNo
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileSerialNo.description: A string showing the serial number of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileIssuer.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileIssuer
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileIssuer.description: A string showing the issuer of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileSubject.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileSubject
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileSubject.description: A string showing the subject of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileValidBegin.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileValidBegin
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileValidBegin.description: A string showing the valid start date of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileValidEnd.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileValidEnd
ilomCtrlLdapSslCertFileValidEnd.description: A string showing the valid end date of the certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingEnabled.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingEnabled
ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingEnabled.description: Specifies whether or not the optional UserMapping feature is enabled. When this feature is enabled, a typical Manager style ldap bind is done first using the specified credentials for the bindDn and bindPw. Then, the user's login name is used as part of the search/filter criteria defined in the attribute-info to obtain the user's official Distinguished Name.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingAttrInfo.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingAttrInfo
ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingAttrInfo.description: The attribute information used to lookup the user login name to the user's Distinguished Name (DN). Typically, it looks very much like a standard LDAP query or filter. The <USERNAME> prefix will be replaced with the login name as part of the query eg: (&(objectclass=person)(uid=<USERNAME>)).

ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingBindDn.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingBindDn
ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingBindDn.description: The Distinguished Name used for the manager style ldap bind so that user lookups can be done.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingBindPw.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingBindPw
ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingBindPw.description: The password string used for the manager style ldap bind.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingSearchBase.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingSearchBase
ilomCtrlLdapSslOptUsrMappingSearchBase.description: The search based used to attempt the user name look up as defined in the attribute information above.

ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainTable.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainTable
ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainTable.description: This table is used to configure domain information required for configuring the LDAP/SSL client.

ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainEntry.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainEntry
ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainEntry.description: An entry for an LDAP/SSL user domain.

ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainId.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainId
ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomainId.description: An integer identifier of the LDAP/SSL domain.

ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomain.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomain
ilomCtrlLdapSslUserDomain.description: This string should match exactly with an authentication domain on the LDAP/SSL server. This string should contain a substitution string '<USERNAME>' which will be replaced with the user's login name during authentication. Either the principle or distinguished name format is allowed.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupsTable.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupsTable
ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupsTable.description: This table is used to configure Admin Group information required for configuring the LDAP/SSL client.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupsEntry.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupsEntry
ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupsEntry.description: An entry for an LDAP/SSL Admin Group.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupId.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupId
ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupId.description: An integer identifier of the LDAP/SSL AdminGroup entry.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupName.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupName
ilomCtrlLdapSslAdminGroupName.description: This string should contain a distinguished name that exactly matches one of the group names on the LDAP/SSL server. Any user belonging to one of these groups in this table will be assigned the ILOM role of Administrator.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupsTable.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupsTable
ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupsTable.description: This table is used to configure Operator Group information required for configuring the LDAP/SSL client.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupsEntry.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupsEntry
ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupsEntry.description: An entry for an LDAP/SSL Operator Group.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupId.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupId
ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupId.description: An integer identifier of the LDAP/SSL Operator Group entry.

ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupName.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupName
ilomCtrlLdapSslOperatorGroupName.description: This string should contain a distinguished name that exactly matches one of the group names on the LDAP/SSL server. Any user belonging to one of these groups in this table will be assigned the ILOM role of Operator.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerTable.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerTable
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerTable.description: This table is used to view and configure alternate server information for the LDAP/SSL client.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerEntry.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerEntry
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerEntry.description: An entry for an LDAP/SSL alternate server table.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerId.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerId
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerId.description: An integer identifier of the LDAP/SSL alternate server table.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerIp.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerIp
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerIp.description: The IP address of the LDAP/SSL alternate server used as directory server for user accounts.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerPort.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerPort
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerPort.description: Specifies the port number for the LDAP/SSL alternate server. Specifying 0 as the port indicates that auto-select will use the well known port number. Specifying 1-65535 is used to explicitly set the port number.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertStatus.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertStatus
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertStatus.description: A string indicating the status of the certificate file. This is useful in determining whether a certificate file is present or not.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertURI.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertURI
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertURI.description: This is the URI of a certificate file needed when Strict Cert Mode is enabled. Setting the URI causes the tranfer of the file, making the certificate available immediately for certificate authentication. Additionally, either 'remove' or 'restore' are supported for direct certificate manipulation.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertClear.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertClear
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertClear.description: A variable that will clear the certificate info associated with the server when it is set to true.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertVersio.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertVersion
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertVersio.description: A string indicating the certificate version of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertSerial.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertSerialNo
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertSerial.description: A string showing the serial number of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertIssuer.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertIssuer
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertIssuer.description: A string showing the issuer of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertSubjec.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertSubject
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertSubjec.description: A string showing the subject of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertValidB.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertValidBegin
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertValidB.description: A string showing the valid start date of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertValidE.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertValidEnd
ilomCtrlLdapSslAlternateServerCertValidE.description: A string showing the valid end date of the alternate server certificate file.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupsTable.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupsTable
ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupsTable.description: This table is used to configure custom group information required for configuring the LDAP/SSL client.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupsEntry.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupsEntry
ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupsEntry.description: An entry for an LDAP/SSLcustom group.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupId.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupId
ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupId.description: An integer identifier of the LDAP/SSL custom group entry.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupName.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupName
ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupName.description: This string should contain a distinguished name that exactly matches one of the group names on the LDAP/SSL server. Any user belonging to one of these groups in this table will be assigned the ILOM role based on the entry's configuration for roles.

ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupRoles.name: ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupRoles
ilomCtrlLdapSslCustomGroupRoles.description: Specifies the role that a user authenticated via LDAP/SSL should have. Setting this property to legacy roles of 'Administrator' or 'Operator', or any of the individual role IDs of 'a', 'u', 'c', 'r', 'o' and 's' will cause the LDAP/SSL client to ignore the schema stored on the LDAP/SSL server. Setting this to 'none' clears the value and indicates that the native LDAP/SSL schema should be used. The role IDs can be joined together 'aucros' where a-admin, u-user, c-console, r-reset, s-service and o-readOnly.

ilomCtrlDNSdhcpAutoDns.name: ilomCtrlDNSdhcpAutoDns
ilomCtrlDNSdhcpAutoDns.description: Specifies whether or not DHCP autodns is enabled.

ilomCtrlDNSTimeout.name: ilomCtrlDNSTimeout
ilomCtrlDNSTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds to wait before timing out if the server does not respond.

ilomCtrlDNSRetries.name: ilomCtrlDNSRetries
ilomCtrlDNSRetries.description: Specifies the number of times a request is attempted again, after a timeout.
